      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"coincidence\" is exactly the problem. The data might reflect real-world patterns, but by automating and scaling those patterns, you are reinforcing a cycle of disinvestment in those communities. You aren't just reflecting reality; you're actively making it worse by suppressing home equity for those families. An audit will prove that your model lacks the nuance to distinguish between \"market trends\" and illegal discriminatory practices. Why should we keep a system online that essentially functions as a tool for redlining?",
